Which option to the ls command displays the ownership attributes, including user andgroup owners of a given file or directory?
A)  - o
B)  - a
C)  - l
D)  - d
C
C. The - l option displays ownership information, including user and group owners of afile or directory. The - o option only shows the user but does not display the group. Theother options shown are not valid for this purpose.
